FBIS3-11774 "drlat059_a_94014" FBIS-LAT-94-059 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Mar 1994 Caribbean Cuba Ross, Rizo Exchange Ideas with Camaguey Workers FL2603151694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0000 GMT 26 Mar 94 FL2603151694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] Politburo members Pedro Ross Leal, who is also secretary general of the Cuban Workers Federation, and Julian Rizo, exchanged ideas and experience with union leaders from Camaguey on the development of the workers' parliaments in workplaces. Ross and Rizo outlined in a general manner the 3,919 parliaments held with a total of almost 30,000 meetings in which [words indistinct] and 80 percent by the labor force. Ross Leal said that this process has not ended, but that it will continue to give an answer to each of the questions which will have a practical solution in each territory, center, or organization.
